First Lady Melania Trump and Second Lady Karen Pence traveled to Fort Bragg to honor members and families of the United States Armed Forces. They were accompanied by Secretary of the Army Dr. Mark Esper. They met with commanders of the United States Army Special Operations Command and observed elite capability demonstrations. They also attended a student assembly at Albritton Middle School on Fort Bragg in honor of Month of the Military Child. Before departing, Mrs. Trump delivered remarks thanking the military personnel for their service and recognizing the sacrifices made by military families.